    "created_at": "2020-03-20T12:53:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2020-03-20T12:53:46Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It looks like the history is accessible from the node repl. I created a very simple test file to check it out, and it appears that you can just access `repl.history` and get a list of all repl history. However, I don't think printing it is included in a builtin command.\r\n\r\nTest file:\r\n```js\r\nconst repl = require('repl')\r\n\r\nconst activeRepl = repl.start('> ')\r\nactiveRepl.on('exit', () => {\r\n  console.log(activeRepl.history)\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nOutput:\r\n```js\r\n> 2 + 2\r\n4\r\n> 4 + 0\r\n4\r\n> .exit\r\n[ '.exit', '4 + 0', '2 + 2' ]\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt also looks like the [repl.history](https://www.npmjs.com/package/repl.history) package can be used to persist this history across executions of `truffle console`. Do we want persistent history, or in-memory?\r\n\r\nIt makes sense to add a `.history` command to the repl that prints x lines of history (perhaps with a cli parameter for the number of lines?).\r\n\r\nIf you agree on implementing it like this, I could look into integrating that into the existing `truffle console` and `truffle develop` commands.",
